properties.sfomuseum:creditline: Gift of the Captain John B. Russell Family
properties.sfomuseum:description: a. Airmail flight cover, Pan American Airways, first Pacific survey flight from California to Hawaii; red stamped “First flight” cachet at right; postmarked April [illegible], 1935 in San Francisco and April 17, 1935 in Honolulu with football-shaped and wavy cancellations over two 6-cent stamps; backstamp: April 16, 1935, Alameda.b. Backing sheet with two sets of mounting corners, with handwritten caption: “April 1935 - Pan American survey flight - San Francisco to Hawaii”, and black and white photographic image of Pan American Clipper Captain Edwin Musick and First Officer R.O.D. Sullivan in cockpit.
